/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:44:**Why it's unique:** 8 independent derivation paths all converge on the same theory (spectral dimension, entanglement bootstrap, most general renormalizable action, asymptotic freedom, Lee-Wick gravity, asymptotic safety, agravity, Weinberg's program). The minimal axiom set is: Lorentz invariance + diffeomorphism invariance + locality + perturbative renormalizability + unitarity. Relaxing any one opens alternatives; keeping all five forces QG+F.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:48:- Six-derivative correction resolves the spectral index tension (predicts n_s ~ 0.974, r ~ 0.0045)
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:93:**What it forces:** All ghost-free nonlocal theories (infinite-derivative gravity, etc.) give d_s → 0, not d_s = 2. This means you face a hard choice: accept ghost-like degrees of freedom (fakeon), break Lorentz invariance (Horava-Lifshitz), or abandon d_s = 2. Appears to be a new mathematical result.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:316:   - *Hidden zeros and theory unification (2024–25):* phi³, pion, and gluon amplitudes share kinematic zeros revealed by geometry; a one-parameter deformation connects all three. At 1-loop, hidden zeros fix the integrand — locality and unitarity emerge for non-SUSY theories.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:486:**The formula:** For SU(2) lattice gauge theory, d²S/dt² = (β/4) Σ□ [|w□|² cos(θ□/2) - L⃗□ · b⃗□], where w□ = covariant derivative, L⃗ = Σ_{i<j} w⃗ᵢ × w⃗ⱼ (commutator angular momentum), b⃗ = su(2) part of U□, cos(θ/2) = Re Tr(U□)/2. Decomposes as C = C_curv (PSD, curvature bonus) + C_comm (indefinite, cross-product terms).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:540:- SQG-NS structural gap: SQG succeeds via commutator coupling (scalar, linear, first-order cancellation), not by beating the Chebyshev chain. NS fails because vector truncation breaks div-free (topological obstruction), coupling is quadratic, and CZ gives only second-order consolidation.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/promising-findings.md:544:**Honest limits:** Sharpness is within the De Giorgi framework only. Profile decomposition, concentration-compactness, stochastic methods, or entirely new frameworks might bypass De Giorgi. The result proves the specific tool is exhausted, not that NS regularity is impossible. The β = 1+s/n formula is elementary (dimensional analysis) — novelty is in explicit tabulation, not in the formula itself.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md:11:All 5 features extracted. Lin simplifies the ε-criterion to C(r)+D(r) < ε₀ (drops A,E). Localization via blow-up/compactness/contradiction instead of cutoff functions — same Young steps are present but hidden in compactness infrastructure. Same covering argument, same scaling exponents, same P¹(Σ)=0 conclusion. Key insight: C(r) alone gives only dim ≤ 2; dim ≤ 1 specifically requires reintroducing E(r) from the dissipation integral. Lin's proof is a streamlining, not a structural departure. It hides lossiness rather than eliminating it.
