/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:18:- The kill condition is too soft. "Cannot be made concrete" will be easy to evade by writing a superficially tidy memo with informal categories. The chain needs a harder failure test, such as requiring one worked example that clearly passes and one that clearly fails under the stated admissibility rule.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:39:- "Name the exact bottleneck term or theorem gap" is the right demand, but the chain does not require any quantitative target. Changing a bottleneck how much? By derivative count, exponent, cancellation, coercivity, compactness, or propagation time? Without a gain metric, attachment can still be cosmetic.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:50:- "Supposed gain is only cosmetic" is again a vulnerable phrase. Cosmetic relative to what closure scheme? A gain that is cosmetic for De Giorgi may be decisive for concentration-compactness or Lagrangian persistence. Because the chain spans multiple architectures, the anti-cosmetic test needs architecture-specific criteria, not one global slogan.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:74:The chain claims to rank mechanisms spanning critical elements, tensor routes, Lagrangian routes, and possibly stochastic structures. Those routes have different currencies of progress: compactness, coercivity, localization stability, propagation, or dynamical rigidity. Without a common scoring rubric, "ranking" is largely evaluator preference disguised as output discipline.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:101:If this chain is kept, it should be interpreted primarily as a falsification chain, not a discovery-ranking chain. The honest success condition is not "produce 1-2 promoted discriminators." It is "show, under a strict admissibility and comparability standard, whether any candidate survives contact with a named bottleneck in a way that is stronger than slogan-level Tao discrimination." Without that tightening, the most likely output is a polished ranking memo with weak epistemic content.
