/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The main repair is not to discard the chain. It is to harden the admissibility standard, move feasibility checks earlier, police overlap more explicitly, and stop forcing a single ranking when the candidates do not share one comparison currency.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-01.md:17:The attacker is also right that the chain needs a harder calibration test than "make it concrete." A worked example that clearly passes the admissibility rule and one that clearly fails should be required up front. Without that, later judgments can stay rhetorical while looking disciplined.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-01.md:47:This lands both at Step 5 and at the structural level. "Promote at most two discriminators" manufactures clarity without first justifying commensurability. The original chain can fairly compare candidates only when they share the same architecture and gain currency. Outside that, it should bucket outcomes rather than force a unified ranking.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-01.md:80:2. Fix the comparison granularity explicitly and require one passing and one failing worked example under the admissibility rule.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-01.md:84:6. Require one primary architecture, one named bottleneck, and one quantitative gain currency for each survivor; allow a coupled secondary route only if it still serves the same bottleneck.
