/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:12:The attack overstates one point: the compactness-rigidity pivot is not illegitimate just because it is familiar. The problem was not the general template. The problem was that the original chain had not yet made the template executable in a Navier-Stokes-specific way.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:27:- a compactness notion usable by the later rigidity step.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:35:The original levers were categories, not mechanisms. Also, "unavailable to Tao's averaged model" is too weak to serve as a hard admission criterion. It can still be used as a secondary filter, but only after a candidate quantity is shown to be defined on the actual compactness class and to offer a concrete contradiction mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:41:This sequencing objection is correct. The hypothetical critical element determines what regularity, compactness, pressure control, and normalization are actually available. Those facts should discipline rigidity selection. The refined chain therefore moves critical-object formulation ahead of final rigidity promotion.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:53:The original "first missing NS-specific lemma" idea was directionally good but under-specified. The refined chain now requires that the first missing lemma be strictly narrower than arbitrary finite-energy regularity and use the compactness-normalized class in an essential way. It also distinguishes failure modes:
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:55:- rigidity quantity not closed under the compactness limit;
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:95:- The most plausible success mode is not a full compactness-rigidity closure, but a theorem-like conditional program or a sharp obstruction located at extraction, stability, definability, or coercivity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:21:The attacker is right that a theorem proved only for minimal packets may miss redundancy, distributed role assignment, or small tails. The attacker is also right that a forced ledger can overstate importance if it counts channels that are dynamically negligible or cancellation-prone. But starting with minimal packets is still a reasonable calibration move. The defect was not using them first; it was letting them implicitly define the whole theorem class.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:39:The original finish allowed only two clean endings: positive leakage bound or explicit vanishing-leakage family. That misses the likely middle case where the route fails because the observable is not invariant enough, the cancellations destroy coercivity, or the bound depends too strongly on packet-class choices. The refined chain should permit that meta-obstruction as a presentable output.
