/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:32:- The nonlocality issue is not cosmetic. Even if the tube core is perfectly aligned, exterior vorticity can still generate critical strain at that point. So a local deficit on the intense-vorticity set may control only the self-induced part of the interaction while leaving the dangerous remainder untouched.
