+# Exploration 002 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Freeze the burden ledger for the active reformulation-audit chain by selecting
+one theorem-facing baseline burden, one admissible gain notion, a typed burden
+ledger with explicit currencies, a same-currency comparability rule, and a
+mandatory transfer-lemma rule for cross-currency claims.
+
+## Method
+
+- Read the cited local architecture, obstruction-screening, and mission-planning
+  notes.
+- Extract the theorem-facing burden language already frozen by the branch.
+- Propose only ledger structure that is supported by those sources.
+- Avoid deriving reformulated equations or nominating candidate families.
+
+## Running Findings
+
+### Initial skeleton
+
+- [VERIFIED] Report initialized before synthesis so findings can be appended
+  incrementally.
+
+### Frozen local audit frame
+
+- [VERIFIED] The active reformulation audit already fixes the inherited
+  architecture to `local-energy flux/localization`, not De Giorgi truncation,
+  stretching localization, or a later compactness-rigidity framework.
+  Source:
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-architecture-screening/local-energy-flux-localization-is-the-right-inherited-architecture-for-the-exact-rewrite-audit.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The live bad term is the localized LEI cutoff-flux bundle
+  `I_flux[phi] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi`, and the whole bundle stays fixed
+  during candidate comparison.
+  Source:
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-architecture-screening/the-localized-lei-cutoff-flux-bundle-is-the-fixed-bad-term-for-the-audit.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The localization regime is one shared CKN-style parabolic cylinder
+  with one standard smooth cutoff; projection, Calderon-Zygmund, Biot-Savart,
+  and cutoff-commutator costs must be repaid in that same package.
+  Source:
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/freeze-one-ckn-style-parabolic-cutoff-protocol-for-the-rewrite-audit.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The fixed solution class is suitable weak solutions in the
+  Leray-Hopf energy class with LEI available; candidates do not get credit for
+  changing that class.
+  Sources:
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/suitable-weak-leray-hopf-with-lei-is-the-fixed-solution-class.md`
+  and
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/every-rewrite-must-stay-inside-the-same-localized-lei-package.md`
+
+### Gain currency evidence
+
+- [VERIFIED] The branch-level gain currency already frozen by the exact-rewrite
+  screens is `coefficient shrinkage in the fixed localized LEI balance`.
+  Source:
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-architecture-screening/success-requires-a-smaller-effective-lei-cutoff-flux-cost-in-the-same-protocol.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The Tao-screen synthesis restates the same standard mechanically:
+  a candidate survives only if it makes an exact term or coefficient smaller on
+  the same fixed `I_flux[phi]` ledger.
+  Source:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-006-exploration-003-unified-tao-verdict.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The planning chain requires one typed ledger with explicit
+  currencies, same-currency comparison only, and an explicit transfer lemma for
+  cross-currency claims.
+  Sources:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`
+  and
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/winning-chain.md`
+
+### Clarifying nearby but different ledgers
+
+- [VERIFIED] `step-008` found that `compactness debt` is the best local fit for
+  a later contradiction-style branch only because temporal packaging and the
+  bridge from the LEI floor to a critical-element program are still missing.
+  Source:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-008-exploration-002-one-ledger-coherence.md`
+- [INFERRED] That does **not** override the active reformulation-audit ledger.
+  For the present chain, the theorem-facing object is still the fixed localized
+  LEI cutoff-flux burden; `compactness input` belongs as one typed currency
+  column, but not as the primary burden or admissible gain notion.
+- [VERIFIED] This distinction is reinforced by the host-space screens:
+  compactness prestige or scale-invariant appearance does not count unless it
+  comes with an architecture-compatible package or an explicit bridge back to
+  the inherited LEI framework.
+  Sources:
+  `library/meta/obstruction-screening/host-space-admission-requires-architecture-compatibility-not-just-compactness-prestige.md`
+  and
+  `library/meta/obstruction-screening/scale-invariant-appearance-inside-lei-does-not-by-itself-clear-a-host-space-audit.md`
+
+## Failed Attempts / Dead Ends
+
+- [VERIFIED] I checked whether the local record had already replaced the
+  theorem-facing LEI burden with a compactness-rigidity burden. It had not:
+  the only compactness-side verdict on disk is a later-branch
+  `[PROPOSED] compactness debt` recommendation under missing temporal and bridge
+  packages, not a rewrite-audit replacement.
+- [VERIFIED] I checked whether any cited source froze an admissible gain notion
+  weaker than coefficient shrinkage, such as derivative-count improvement,
+  exponent improvement, or a purely representational cancellation claim. The
+  exact-rewrite screens reject those unless they cash out back into a smaller
+  coefficient on the same localized LEI balance.
+
+## Provisional Synthesis
+
+### Frozen Step-1 verdict
+
+- [PROPOSED] Baseline burden to freeze:
+  the full effective closure burden of the fixed localized LEI cutoff-flux
+  bundle
+  `I_flux[phi] = ∬_{Q_r} (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi`
+  in one CKN-style cutoff protocol and the suitable-weak / Leray-Hopf + LEI
+  solution class, **after** pressure recovery, projection / CZ debt,
+  Biot-Savart or reconstruction debt, cutoff commutators, and admissibility
+  obligations are restored.
+- [PROPOSED] Admissible gain notion to freeze:
+  `strict net coefficient shrinkage of that same fixed I_flux[phi] burden in
+  the same localized LEI inequality, under the same cutoff protocol and
+  solution class, after all visible debts are charged`.
+- [INFERRED] This is the narrowest theorem-facing freeze consistent with the
+  active branch. It blocks two errors at once:
+  1. calling a surrogate gain theorem-facing before it returns to the LEI
+     balance;
+  2. letting later contradiction or host-space rhetoric silently replace the
+     exact-rewrite audit.
+
+### Typed burden ledger
+
+- [PROPOSED] Every later candidate packet should record entries with the
+  following schema:
+  `currency | compared object | stage | claimed sign | explicit debt restored |
+  theorem-facing cash-out sentence | status`
+  where `stage` must be one of:
+  `pre-localization`, `post-localization`, `post-recovery`, `post-admissibility`,
+  or `theorem-facing cash-out`.
+- [PROPOSED] The frozen currencies are:
+
+| currency | typed meaning in this chain | what can count as a gain | what records debt |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `derivative count` | derivative order landing on the live localized term or on debt terms after cutoff insertion | fewer derivatives on the same live post-localization object, but only if the theorem-facing cash-out returns to a smaller `I_flux[phi]` coefficient | derivatives moved onto cutoff, projector, pressure recovery, Biot-Savart reinsertion, or commutators |
+| `locality` | whether the post-localization expression remains local in `(u,p)` or reintroduces nonlocal operators in the fixed cylinder | less nonlocal structure on the same post-localization object, again only if it shrinks the same LEI burden after repayment | Helmholtz projection, CZ kernels, harmonic pressure splitting, Biot-Savart reinsertion, far-field tails |
+| `cancellation` | exact algebraic cancellation that survives cutoff insertion and later admissibility | a cancellation that still survives once absolute values, localization, and debt restoration are imposed, yielding a smaller coefficient on the same live term | cancellations that disappear after localization, after reconstruction, or after pressure re-entry |
+| `integrability` | concrete spacetime norm demand inside the fixed suitable-weak / LEI package | weaker norm demand on the same localized object without upgrading the solution class, plus same-ledger cash-out | stronger exponents, auxiliary norms, or closure requirements not already available in the fixed class |
+| `pressure recoverability` | ability to reconstruct or control the `p u · ∇phi` contribution inside the same protocol | a pressure handling route that returns the same localized LEI balance with a smaller net coefficient on the flux bundle | any new singular-integral bound, harmonic splitting, projection debt, or pressure term that must be repaid |
+| `admissibility` | compatibility with suitable weak Leray-Hopf plus LEI, without changing framework | no extra admissibility debt beyond the frozen class, with same-ledger cash-out | any reliance on mild/classical solutions, stronger regularity, different closure scheme, or endpoint drift |
+| `compactness input` | explicit contribution to a later extraction / stability / contradiction package that still names the LEI-floor bridge | only informative at this stage unless an explicit transfer lemma sends it back to the frozen LEI burden | compactness rhetoric without a bridge, temporal package, or theorem-facing LEI cash-out |
+| `scaling compatibility` | relation of the candidate quantity to the frozen parabolic CKN scaling and cutoff regime | only informative unless it produces a same-ledger smaller coefficient on `I_flux[phi]` | claims that depend on changing region, rescaling conventions, or a merely scale-invariant surrogate quantity |
+
+- [INFERRED] In this ledger, only the final `theorem-facing cash-out sentence`
+  can certify a live gain. The other currencies are bookkeeping languages for
+  gains and debts, not substitute success criteria.
+
+### Same-currency comparability rule
+
+- [PROPOSED] Two entries are comparable only if all of the following match:
+  `currency`, `compared object`, `stage`, `cutoff protocol`, `solution class`,
+  and `debt restoration status`.
+- [PROPOSED] A claimed improvement is same-currency only when it changes the
+  same typed object in the same stage. Examples:
+  - derivative-count on a pre-localization identity is **not** comparable to
+    derivative-count on the post-recovery LEI term;
+  - cancellation before cutoff insertion is **not** comparable to cancellation
+    after pressure recovery;
+  - compactness input is **not** comparable to coefficient shrinkage on
+    `I_flux[phi]`.
+- [PROPOSED] The only theorem-facing win condition is stricter still:
+  two packets are comparable for promotion only if both cash out to the same
+  localized LEI inequality with the same frozen bad term `I_flux[phi]`, and
+  one returns a strictly smaller net coefficient after the same debts are paid.
+
+### Mandatory transfer-lemma rule
+
+- [PROPOSED] A transfer lemma is mandatory whenever a claim crosses any one of
+  these boundaries:
+  - one currency to another;
+  - one stage to another;
+  - one object to another;
+  - candidate-native variables to the `(u,p)` LEI ledger;
+  - a surrogate term to the frozen bad term `I_flux[phi]`.
+- [PROPOSED] The lemma must be named and must state:
+  `source currency/object/stage`,
+  `target currency/object/stage`,
+  the hypotheses used,
+  the debts repaid during transfer,
+  and the exact theorem-facing inequality returned at the end.
+- [PROPOSED] Without that named lemma, the packet must be marked
+  `unresolved cross-currency claim` rather than credited as favorable.
+- [INFERRED] This rule is what blocks silent optimism from the most tempting
+  rewrite slogans:
+  derivative savings, prettier locality, NS-specific cancellation,
+  scale-invariant appearance, and compactness rhetoric all remain non-operative
+  until they are transferred back to the same frozen LEI coefficient language.
+
+### Mechanical use rule for later packets
+
+- [PROPOSED] Each later packet should contain exactly one `baseline burden`
+  line and one `admissible gain` line written verbatim in the frozen language
+  above.
+- [PROPOSED] Every claimed positive effect must appear first in one of the
+  eight currencies and then either:
+  - cash out directly to the same `I_flux[phi]` coefficient language; or
+  - cite a transfer lemma and remain provisional until the cash-out is shown.
+- [PROPOSED] Any packet lacking a same-ledger cash-out or a named transfer
+  lemma should be failed mechanically as `decorative`, `cross-currency`, or
+  `framework-drift`, not left for narrative discretion.
+
+### Outcome
+
+- Outcome: `succeeded`
+- [INFERRED] The active reformulation-audit chain can now use one frozen
+  theorem-facing burden and one admissible gain notion mechanically.
+- [INFERRED] The key distinction is that `compactness input` remains a typed
+  currency entry, but not the primary burden of this exact-rewrite audit.
+
