+# Exploration 002 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  freeze the burden ledger for the active reformulation-audit chain by fixing
+  one theorem-facing baseline burden, one admissible gain notion, explicit
+  ledger currencies, a same-currency comparison rule, and a mandatory
+  transfer-lemma rule.
+- What I tried:
+  read the cited exact-rewrite architecture files, the obstruction-screening
+  rules, the unified Tao-screen verdict, the step-008 one-ledger coherence
+  memo, and the active chain documents; then separated the active LEI
+  reformulation ledger from the later compactness-rigidity bookkeeping ideas.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`
+- One key takeaway:
+  the active audit must stay frozen on the localized LEI cutoff-flux burden
+  `I_flux[phi]`, and the only admissible gain is strict net coefficient
+  shrinkage on that same burden after all localization, recovery, and
+  admissibility debts are repaid.
+- Frozen baseline burden:
+  [PROPOSED] the full effective closure burden of
+  `I_flux[phi] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi`
+  in the shared CKN-style cutoff protocol and suitable-weak / Leray-Hopf + LEI
+  class, after pressure recovery, projection / CZ, reconstruction,
+  commutator, and admissibility debt are restored.
+- Frozen admissible gain notion:
+  [PROPOSED] strict net coefficient shrinkage of that same fixed
+  `I_flux[phi]` burden in the same localized LEI inequality.
+- Frozen ledger currencies:
+  `derivative count`, `locality`, `cancellation`, `integrability`,
+  `pressure recoverability`, `admissibility`, `compactness input`,
+  `scaling compatibility`.
+- Same-currency rule:
+  [PROPOSED] compare only entries with the same currency, same object, same
+  stage, same cutoff protocol, same solution class, and same debt-restoration
+  status; promotion requires both packets to cash out to the same localized LEI
+  inequality with the same fixed bad term `I_flux[phi]`.
+- Transfer-lemma rule:
+  [PROPOSED] any cross-currency, cross-stage, cross-object, surrogate-to-LEI,
+  or candidate-variable-to-`(u,p)` claim must name an explicit transfer lemma
+  stating the source, target, hypotheses, debts repaid, and final theorem-facing
+  inequality; otherwise mark it `unresolved cross-currency claim`.
+- Leads worth pursuing:
+  use this ledger verbatim in later candidate packets so every claimed gain is
+  either same-ledger cash-out or an explicitly unresolved transfer problem.
+- Unexpected findings:
+  `compactness debt` is locally supported only as a proposed bookkeeping choice
+  for a later contradiction-style branch with no frozen bridge from the LEI
+  floor; it should remain a typed currency entry here, not the primary burden.
+- Computations worth doing later:
+  none numerical; the next useful work is packet-level application of this
+  ledger to specific candidate rewrites, with every transfer step named
+  explicitly.
